We have recommended to the Local Chief Executive the following:
Require the LDRRM Officer to include in the LDRRMFIP the list of projects/program/activities chargeable to the unexpended LDRRMF from previous years, and provide columns for the allotment class of the LDRRMF; 
Direct the LDRRMO to prepare and submit the Monthly Report on Sources and Utilization of LDRRMF using the prescribed format (Annex B of COA Circular No. 2012-002) on or before the 15th day after the end of each month through the LDRRMC and Local Development Council (LDC) to the Audit Team. The report shall be prepared and certified correct by the Municipal Accountant-Designate;
Direct the Municipal Budget Officer to maintain separate Registries of Appropriations, Allotments and Obligations (RAAOs) for the LDRRMF as required in Section 5.1.4 of COA Circular No. 2012-002; and
Direct the Municipal Accountant-Designate to strictly comply with Sections 5.1.10 and 5.1.11of COA Circular No. 2012-002 on the treatment of unexpended LDRRMF, which shall be transferred to the Special Trust Fund under the account of Trust Liability-DRMM in the Trust Fund books.

We have recommended to the management for executive and legislative action:
a. The Municipal Mayor to issue new appointments bearing his original signature;
b. The Sangguniang Bayan to issue sangguniang resolution embodying the concurrence of the majority of all the members of the Sanggunian as to the department heads;
c. The Human Resource Personnel to provide checklist on each personnel for their 201 file whether they have complied the required working experience, education, eligibility, personnel data sheet (pds), medical certificate, certificate of live birth, marriage contract, clearances, performance rating and scholastic record / academic records.
d. Failure to submit the required documents would warrant the issuance of notice of disallowance.

